answerText: Ranier Maria Rilke[10] This semi-autobiographical work was Rilke's only published novel. In it, he speaks of pregnant women as if "there were two fruits: a child and a deaththat were growing inside them."

question: Question: This poet asked whether time "the destroyer" truly exists in the antipenultimate of his Sonnets to Orpheus. For ten points each:  [10] Name this German poet who wrote of a creature "misted with tiredness" in his "The Panther."
